The Alex Jones Show 
Sunday, 23 March 2014


[sebaygo1]

Show description from theweb site :: On the live Sunday, March 23 transmission of Infowars Live, Alex Jones rectifies the media's confusion over the Obamacare penalty after an all-out assault was waged on Internet pioneer Matt Drudge, who on Friday asserted he had just paid the "liberty tax" for not getting covered. Alex also dissects the flopping failure that is Obamacare and marvels at its miserable enrollment figures, which the healthcare law is supposedly dependent upon. 

On today's show, Jones tackles the increasingly volatile situation in Crimea, and analyzes the US government's latest attempt to suppress the First Amendment by way of a new media shield law, which antithetically doesn't "shield" alternative media journalists like activist Mark Dice, a vocal opponent of the Obama administration, who recently had his immensely popular Youtube channel taken down. [restored a few hours later]
